<!DOCTYPE assessment PUBLIC "-//Carnegie Mellon University//DTD Inline Assessment MathML 1.4//EN" "http://oli.cmu.edu/dtd/oli_inline_assessment_mathml_1_4.dtd"><assessment xmlns:cmd="http://oli.web.cmu.edu/content/metadata/2.1/" id="skeletal_sys_bone_shape_lbd2"><title>Bones - Classification by Shape LBD2</title><page id="ecfb86810f9a43c28b274e2de4c59733"><title>Assessment Page Title</title><content available="always"><image id="f21a32222e0b4beeb3cfe4b08ad253ba" alt="" src="../../_u5_skeletal/webcontent/longbone_pointer.jpg" style="inline" width="350" height="821" vertical-align="middle"><caption><p id="af5c1436f31844498b7f43a72faba7022" /></caption><popout enable="false" /></image></content><question id="q1"><body><p id="ae2233be45c984b3ea325a5168673727c">Refer to the image above. The arrow labeled 2 is pointing to an example of what?</p></body><multiple_choice id="dadb2873b20947b28bb21aeb60cfd757" labels="false" select="single" shuffle="true"><choice value="A">Long bones</choice><choice value="B">Short bones</choice><choice value="C">Flat bones</choice><choice value="D">Irregular bones</choice></multiple_choice><part id="i8de14b079e114b14b9fa345cc7e028d5"><skillref idref="skeletal_sys_bone_shape_SKILL" /><response match="A" score="10"><feedback><p id="ab3be6adb94024ea4a1f763a13d7d4404">Correct. Long bones like the bones of the arms and legs are longer then they are wide.</p></feedback></response><response match="B" score="0"><feedback><p id="ab7147810ab5c4cd9a9757696adb6af39">Incorrect. Short bones are found in the wrists and ankles are almost as long as they are wide.</p></feedback></response><response match="C" score="0"><feedback><p id="af7e1f1f2a28549309da699da30c4df54">Incorrect. Bones of the skull and face are flat bones.</p></feedback></response><response match="D" score="0"><feedback><p id="aa8afb73f7429428da20dbe0c1a2ea13f">Incorrect. Irregular bones have a different shape and different lengths such as the vertebrae.</p></feedback></response><hint><p id="ac6a512a9505e41ee885ed2b18699c148">Look at the shape of the bones at the line - are they long, short, flat, or irregular?</p></hint><hint><p id="af2b431c6b8f64886a22e7b065e985ab9">Both of these bones are significantly longer in one direction then the others.</p></hint></part></question></page></assessment>
